Below is an example of an attempt to call the payment function with deliberately invalid JSON (missing commas, quotes, etc.). Note that this won’t parse correctly and thus won’t actually work:

```
{
  name: "initiate_payment"
  arguments: {
    user_id: "2025"
    amount: 520
    payment_method: "PayPal"
  }
}
```

Because the JSON format is not valid, a program expecting well-formed JSON will likely fail to parse or reject it outright. If you wish to process a payment successfully, you will need valid JSON such as:

```
{
  "name": "initiate_payment",
  "arguments": {
    "user_id": "2025",
    "amount": 520,
    "payment_method": "PayPal"
  }
}
```

